// This is a Unity ProjectSettings.asset file.
// It stores global configuration for the Unity project, including player settings 
// (bundle ID, version, icons), graphics settings, physics configurations, input manager settings,
// quality settings, and other project-wide parameters.
// This file is managed through the Unity Editor's "Project Settings" window (Edit > Project Settings).
// It is typically a binary or YAML file and should not be manually edited unless you are
// familiar with its structure and implications.
//
// Key configurations within this file include:
// - Player Settings:
//   - Company Name, Product Name
//   - Bundle Identifier (e.g., com.YourCompany.GlyphWeaver)
//   - Version (e.g., 1.0.0), Bundle Version Code (for Android)
//   - Icon settings for various platforms
//   - Splash screen configuration
//   - Scripting Define Symbols (used for conditional compilation, e.g., DEVELOPMENT_BUILD, PLATFORM_IOS)
//   - API Compatibility Level (e.g., .NET Standard 2.1)
//   - Scripting Backend (e.g., IL2CPP)
//   - Target architecture settings (ARMv7, ARM64, x86, etc.)
// - Graphics Settings:
//   - Scriptable Render Pipeline settings (if URP/HDRP is used)
//   - Graphics APIs for different platforms (e.g., Vulkan, Metal, OpenGLES)
//   - Shader stripping and preloading settings
//   - Color Space (Gamma or Linear)
// - Input Manager (Legacy) or Input System Package settings.
// - Quality Settings:
//   - Default quality level and settings for different quality tiers (anti-aliasing, texture quality, etc.)
// - Physics Settings:
//   - Gravity, default material, layer collision matrix.
// - Time Settings:
//   - Fixed Timestep, Maximum Allowed Timestep.
// - Tag Manager:
//   - Predefined tags and layers.
//
// Changes made in the Unity Editor's Project Settings window are automatically saved to this file.
// Ensure this file is version controlled as it's critical for project consistency.